  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1932</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The photograph features the film crew of the Yugoslav silent movie ‘Sa verom u Boga’ (In God we trust). There is a damaged black car in the centre of the picture driven into a roadside ditch. In the background are some trees and a two-storey house; in the forefront a road.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The silent feature film ‘Sa verom u Boga’ (In God we trust) was shot in Serbia in 1932, when sound movies were already on the rise. The film was directed by the young Mihajlo A. Popović (1908–1990).</ab>
